Apply the power property first ( k log A = log Aᵏ ):

(1/6) log x = log x^{1/6}  
3 log (x + 5) = log (x + 5)^{3}

Now subtracting logarithms turns into the logarithm of a quotient (log A − log B = log (A/B)):

(1/6) log x − 3 log (x + 5)  
= log x^{1/6} − log (x + 5)^{3}  
= log [ x^{1/6} / (x + 5)^{3} ].

Thus the condensed form is  

log ( x^{1/6} / (x + 5)^{3} ).
